{"ts":"2026-07-10T10:50:11.975Z","author":"codex","op":"comment_add","patch":[{"op":"replace","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-07-10T10:50:11.975Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/comments","value":[{"created_at":"2026-07-10T10:50:11.974Z","author":"codex","text":"PR #21 finishing pass (2026-07-10): recovered and critically reviewed partial uncommitted fixes from a prior interrupted agent run. Kept fixes for streamed escaped-quote pairs split at chunk boundaries, CRLF split at chunk boundaries, physical CSV row-number tracking across blank rows, deferred --key index loading until headers validate, and the Levenshtein test comment typo; regenerated dist artifacts. Added exact-boundary regression tests. Verification: npm ci, npm run build, npm test => 89/89 pass; fresh /tmp/fx-pm-csv local install; timeout 20 pm --help returned successfully; real --skip-headers --stream dry-run and import created 2 items including title Stream \"two\"; blank-line streaming dry-run reported empty title at physical Row 5 and create 1/skip 1; malformed header with --stream --key title exited 2 with a single structured CommandError and no stack trace; default no-new-flags dry-run stdout matched origin/main exactly. npm run changelog:full and changelog:check passed. Bot findings accepted: Gemini/Greptile split CRLF, split quote, physical line numbering; cubic those plus deferred key-index load and comment typo. Hound ES6/dist warnings are configuration false positives because TypeScript targets ES2022 and generated dist intentionally uses modern syntax."}]}],"before_hash":"1282b0b20a2857475bc3a313c0611bee81534c165284eba8f661bbdac2934c92","after_hash":"58cd4fb08ef7488cd14beb550331a2d07c35a9e969c3a2211d740ddfb5a9163a"}
